This directory includes an selinux policy for lolproxy. It assumes
the following file locations:

	/usr/sbin/lolproxy		-- binary
	/etc/lolproxy/lolproxy\.cfg	-- configuration
	/var/run/lolproxy\.pid		-- pid-file
	/var/run/lolproxy\.sock(.*)	-- stats socket
	/var/empty/lolproxy		-- chroot dir

To build and load it on RHEL5 you'll need the "selinux-policy-devel" package,
and from within this directory run:

	make -f /usr/share/selinux/devel/Makefile
	sudo semodule -i lolproxy.pp
	restorecon /usr/sbin/lolproxy /etc/lolproxy/lolproxy.cfg /var/run/lolproxy.pid /var/run/lolproxy.sock*


Feedback to Jan-Frode Myklebust <janfrode@tanso.no> is much appreciated,
